detaileddescription.para: Primes, each slightly less than twice its predecessor, and as far away from powers of two as possible.

To minimize space overhead, unlike many hash tables this stores a single value, not a key and a value. Any size of value can be stored, but all the values in the hash table must be the same size, and the values must be safe to copy with memcpy. To get key:value behaviour, simply insert a struct with a key and value into the hash.

parameterdescription.para: A function to test value equality.
The size of the values to be stored.

detaileddescription.para: Return the number of elements in hash.

memberdef.argsstring: (const ZixHash *hash, const void *key, const unsigned h, const unsigned h_nomod)
memberdef.name: find_entry

detaileddescription.para: Search for an item in hash.
If no matching value is found, ZIX_STATUS_SUCCESS will be returned, and inserted will be pointed to the copy of value made in the new hash node.
If a matching value already exists, ZIX_STATUS_EXISTS will be returned, and inserted will be pointed to the existing value.

parameterdescription.para: The copy of value in the hash table.

detaileddescription.para: Call f on each value in hash.

parameterdescription.para: The function to call on each value.
The user_data parameter passed to f.
